<structure name="simple_present">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Present Tense Verb] + [Object]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Je mange une pomme</french>
        <english>I eat an apple</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 2. Near Future (Futur Proche)
```xml
<structure name="near_future">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Aller in present] + [Infinitive]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Nous allons partir</french>
        <english>We are going to leave</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 3. Basic Question with Est-ce que
```xml
<structure name="basic_question">
    <pattern>Est-ce que + [Subject] + [Verb] + [Object]?</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Est-ce que tu aimes le café?</french>
        <english>Do you like coffee?</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 4. Simple Passé Composé
```xml
<structure name="passe_compose">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Avoir in present] + [Past Participle] + [Object]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>J'ai mangé du pain</french>
        <english>I ate some bread</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 5. Basic Negation
```xml
<structure name="negation">
    <pattern>[Subject] + ne + [Verb] + pas + [Object]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Je ne veux pas de sucre</french>
        <english>I don't want sugar</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 6. Simple Description
```xml
<structure name="description">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Être] + [Adjective]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>La maison est grande</french>
        <english>The house is big</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 7. Basic Time Expression
```xml
<structure name="time_expression">
    <pattern>[Time Expression] + [Subject] + [Verb] + [Object]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Aujourd'hui je vais au marché</french>
        <english>Today I go to the market</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 8. Simple Comparison
```xml
<structure name="comparison">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Verb] + plus/moins + [Adjective] + que</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Il est plus grand que moi</french>
        <english>He is taller than me</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 9. Basic Opinion
```xml
<structure name="opinion">
    <pattern>Je pense que + [Subject] + [Verb] + [Object]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Je pense que c'est bon</french>
        <english>I think that it's good</english>
    </example>
</structure>

## 10. Simple Location
```xml
<structure name="location">
    <pattern>[Subject] + [Être/Verb] + [Preposition] + [Place]</pattern>
    <example>
        <french>Le livre est sur la table</french>
        <english>The book is on the table</english>
    </example>
</structure>